.\" Man page for ocode
.\" Generated from the help output
.TH OCODE 1 "June 2025" "ocode" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ocode \- AI coding agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ocode
[\fIglobal options\fR] \fIcommand\fR [\fIcommand options\fR]
.PP
.B ocode
[\fITUI options\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ocode
is an AI-powered coding agent that helps you write, edit, and understand code.
It can run interactively in a terminal UI (TUI), headlessly for automation,
or as a server with a web interface.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Show help message and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Show version information and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBrun\fR
Run a prompt non-interactively (headless mode).
.TP
\fBserve\fR
Start the HTTP server with web UI.
.TP
\fBweb\fR
Start server and open browser (alias for \fBserve \-\-open\fR).
.TP
\fBacp\fR
Run ACP (Agent Communication Protocol) server over stdio.
.TP
\fBmcp\fR
Manage MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers.
.TP
\fBmodels\fR
List available models.
.TP
\fBskills\fR
Manage skills.
.TP
\fBversion\fR
Show version information.
.SH TUI MODE
When invoked without a command, ocode starts the interactive terminal UI.
.TP
\fB\-session \fI<id>\fR
Resume a specific session by ID.
.TP
\fB\-continue\fR
Continue the most recent session.
.TP
\fB\-yolo\fR, \fB\-\-yolo\fR, \fB\-\-dangerously\-skip\-permissions\fR
Auto-approve all permission prompts.
.TP
\fB\-\-permission\-mode \fI<auto|off>\fR
Set permission mode (default: auto).
.SH COMMAND-SPECIFIC HELP
Run \fBocode \fIcommand\fR \fB\-h\fR for command-specific help.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.config/opencode/config.json\fR
User configuration file.
.TP
\fI~/.config/opencode/skills/\fR
User-installed skills directory.
.TP
\fI~/.local/share/opencode/sessions/\fR
Session storage directory.
.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
\fBOPENCODE_MODEL\fR
Default model to use (e.g., \fBgpt-4\fR, \fBclaude-3-opus\fR).
.TP
\fBOPENCODE_SERVER_USERNAME\fR
Basic auth username for the HTTP server.
.TP
\fBOPENCODE_SERVER_PASSWORD\fR
Basic auth password for the HTTP server.
.TP
\fBNO_COLOR\fR
Disable colored output when set.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Start the interactive TUI:
.B ocode
.TP
Run a one-off prompt:
.B ocode run "How do I read a file in Go?"
.TP
Run with a specific model:
.B ocode run -model gpt-4 -prompt "Write a hello world"
.TP
Start the web server and open browser:
.B ocode web
.TP
List available models:
.B ocode models
.TP
List models from a specific provider:
.B ocode models --provider anthropic
.TP
Manage MCP servers:
.B ocode mcp list
.TP
Install skills:
.B ocode skills install
